Executive Profile
Stephen Jon Carlotti  Executive Vice President of Marketing, The Michaels Companies, Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 0 Board Members in 0 different organizations across 4 different industries.50$994,788As of Fiscal Year 2016
Background

		Mr. Stephen Jon Carlotti, also known as Steve, has been Executive Vice President of Marketing at Michaels Stores, Inc. since June 17, 2014. Mr. Carlotti has been an Executive Vice President of Marketing at The Michaels Companies, Inc. since June 17, 2014. Mr. Carlotti served as the Chief Executive Officer of The Cambridge Group, Inc. He served as Senior Partner of Prophet, Inc. He has 20 years of experience working for consumer and retail companies. He served as Executive ... Vice President, Global Practices and Consulting Services at Nielsen from June 2011 to October 2011 He served in various capacities at McKinsey & Company since 1990, including as Senior Partner from 2005 to June 2010. Mr. Carlotti is an advisory board member of E&J Gallo Winery. His work cuts across a range of functional areas including strategy, marketing, sales force effectiveness and supply chain (especially when it drives customer satisfaction). He worked for McKinsey & Company in Chicago, where he led Midwestern Consumer/Retail Practice as well as its North American Consumer Marketing Practice. He focused on growth, strategy and marketing issues for clients in the consumer products, retail and automotive industries, among others. His clients included Sara Lee, Alticor, Office Depot, E&J Gallo, AT&T and Ford. Mr. Carlotti graduated second in his class from Dartmouth in 1988. He holds a Masters in Public Administration from Woodrow Wilson School at Princeton.Read Full Background




